<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1911-11-01T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1911-11-01T00:00:00-05:00" n="140" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d140">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File 893.51/630.</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                    to the <gloss type="to">American Chargé
                                d’Affaires</gloss></hi>.</head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Extract.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                        <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1911-11-01">
                                        <hi rend="italic">November 1, 1911</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>The Department has been informed by the American group that a loan
                                such as reported in your telegram of October 28 would seriously
                                affect the issue of the loan for currency reform already agreed upon
                                and might seriously interfere with carrying out that reform as well
                                as adversely affecting China’s credit in future. You may informally
                                request of the Chinese Government further details of any proposed
                                loan.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Knox</hi>.</signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>